Throws:
java.io.IOException
java.lang.ClassNotFoundException

writeObject

private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Save the state of the HashMap instance to a stream.

Serial Data:
The table length of the HashMap (the length of the bucket array) is emitted (int), followed by the size of the HashMap (the number of key-value mappings), followed by the key (Object) and value (Object) for each key-value mapping represented by the HashMap The key-value mappings are emitted in the order that they are returned by entrySet().iterator().
Throws:
java.io.IOException
